  "text": "T cell and B cell immune dysfunction with production of autoantibodies, cytotoxic cell death, in addition to the previously mentioned apoptosis is the classical model of thyrocytes and thyroid follicle destruction. But recently described as non-classic mechanism and not related to cell death, but to the chronic inflammatory process by inhibiting the thyroid function mediated by inflammatory cytokines TNF-and INF-based upon T cell dysfunction, even without a lymphocytic infiltrate, but by exposure per se to inflammatory cytokines [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
